//****************************************************************************
// $Module type: Program (library smoke test)
// $Module name: Dummy.src
// $Author     : Nils Svedmyr, RDC Tools International
//
// Description : Compile canary for RDCToolsLib. This library ships no application of its own,
//               so nothing here ever got compiled in isolation - breakage only surfaced later,
//               inside whichever consumer workspace happened to Use the broken package.
//
//               This program Uses every publishable package in the library. It is not meant to
//               DO anything; the point is that it COMPILES. If it does, the library stands on
//               its own feet: no missing dependency, no broken Use chain, no duplicate class.
//
//               Compile it from RDCToolsLibDev25.0.sws (or 26.0), the maintainer workspace that
//               wires in vwin32fh as the sibling ..\vwin32fh. The consumer-facing
//               RDCToolsLibLibrary*.sws declares no libraries and does not build this - see
//               README.md. vwin32fh is a real dependency of the library (cRDCCJGrid, cRDCLogFile
//               and 8 more Use vWin32fh.pkg), not of this test.
//
// $Rev History:
//    2026-07-22  Turned from the Studio "Basic Project" stub into a real compile canary.
//    2026-07-23  Moved to RDCToolsLibDev*.sws; RDCToolsLibLibrary*.sws is now the pure entry.
//****************************************************************************
Use Windows.pkg
Use cHtmlHelp.pkg
Use cApplication.pkg
Use cConnection.pkg
Use Datadict.pkg

Object oHtmlHelp is a cHtmlHelp
End_Object

Object oApplication is a cApplication

    Object oConnection is a cConnection
        Use LoginEncryption.pkg
        Use DatabaseLoginDialog.dg
    End_Object

End_Object

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// The library surface under test.
//
// THESE MUST STAY BELOW THE cApplication OBJECT. Several packages here depend on
// an application object already existing - cRDCProjectIniFile, for one, reads
// psProgramPath(phoWorkspace(ghoApplication)) while constructing its global
// oRDCProjectIniFile instance. Hoisting the Use lines up to the top of the file,
// which is where they conventionally live and where they started, breaks the
// compile. Resist tidying them back.
//
// Within the block the order is alphabetical and carries no meaning - each
// package Uses whatever else it needs itself.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Use Base64Functions.pkg
